cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on mobile-edge cloud computing in a wireless interference environment, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a distributed computation offloading algorithm for achieving efficient computation offloading, which falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses game theory to formulate the computation offloading decision making problem among mobile device users, which falls under the scope of information theory. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the structural property of the multi-user computation offloading game and derives the upper bound of the convergence time, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper formulates the computation offloading decision making problem among mobile device users as a multi-user computation offloading game and analyzes its Nash equilibrium, which falls under the scope of game theory.
